This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the problem of learning to rank items in a recommender system. It also involves partial feedback, which is a common issue in information retrieval. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The paper deals with natural language processing and recommender systems, which makes it likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. 

The paper involves active exploration of user tastes, which is a common problem in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). 

Finally, the paper involves analysis of the algorithm and proving upper bounds, which makes it likely to belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
